<TEXT>
a federal judge awarded more than 27 
million in damages wednesday to the family of a father and son who 
perished when a small plane collided with an aeromexico jet over 
southern california in 1986 
it was the second case to result in a damage award to relatives 
of people killed in the disaster which claimed 82 lives 
us district judge manuel l real ruled the family was entitled 
to 2733666 in compensation for economic and personal losses due 
to the deaths of joe guzman 45 and his son robert 18 
joe guzmans daughter reann 5 was awarded 427254 of the 
damages 
the norwalk truck driver and his son were on the aeromexico jet 
returning to los angeles from a fishing vacation in baja california 
when the jet collided with a small private plane and crashed into 
suburban cerritos 
the death toll totaled 67 people in the aircraft and 15 people 
in the neighborhood 20 miles southeast of los angeles 
in the first case a different judge awarded about 13 million 
to a san jose man who lost his wife and son in the crash dozens of 
similar cases to determine damages are pending 
the lawsuits are based upon the decision of a federal jury that 
last april blamed the crash equally on the government through the 
actions of an airtraffic controller and on william kramer the 
pilot of the small plane 
</TEXT>
