<TEXT>
president bush is refusing to recognize 
lithuanias breakaway government fearing a replay of 1956 when the 
united states rooted for hungarys uprising but stayed on the 
sidelines as soviet tanks crushed the revolt his spokesman says 
bush in a meeting with balticamericans on wednesday rejected 
their plea for us recognition of lithuania as independent from 
the soviet union 
the balticamericans told the president that lithuania is only 
the beginning of soviet troubles they said separatist movements 
will be boiling over in latvia and estonia by the time soviet 
president mikhail s gorbachev arrives here for his summit with 
bush at the end of may 
the latvians will be declaring independence in two weeks 
estonia is in the same process by the time we get to the summit 
