<TEXT>
with his strong ties to west germany the 
first freely elected leader of east germany lothar de maiziere is 
wellequipped to lead the former communist bastion to unification 
and democracy 
de maiziere was confirmed as prime minister by the countrys 
first democratically elected parliament on thursday after leading 
the alliance for germany to victory in elections march 18 
the 50yearold lawyers political skills were tested in two 
weeks of tough negotiations with other mainstream parties that 
resulted in a broad governing coalition the agreement gives de 
maiziere a twothirds majority needed in parliament to pass 
constitutional changes required for quick unification with west 
germany 
the new prime minister was little known in the west before he 
assumed leadership of the christian democratic union or cdu on 
nov 10 after the opening of east germanys borders 
de maiziere who is married with four children belongs to a 
prominent huguenot family with strong links to west germany his 
uncle ulrich held a top post in the west german army and his 
cousin thomas is spokeman for the cdus sister party in west 
berlin 
de maiziere was born march 2 1940 in nordhausen now an east 
german town close to the west german border 
like many germans he stayed away from politics immediately 
after the trauma of the nazi era and world war ii 
his first love was music and his proficiency in playing the 
viola won him a place in various orchestras in east berlin in the 
1960s 
but the musician was drawn to law he earned a degree from east 
berlins prestigious humboldt university in 1975 
de maiziere made a name for himself by defending conscientious 
objectors and independent political activists 
for many years he headed the lutheran church council 
but the lawyer and musician was also drawn to politics de 
maiziere joined the christian democrats in 1956 when they were 
allied with the communist party but he never numbered among the 
top ranks of party officials 
when communist rule crumbled under popular pressure last fall 
east germany needed credible politicians to manage the crisis and 
help with the merger of the two germanys de maiziere became deputy 
prime minister in the caretaker government of reformminded 
communist hans modrow 
the governing christian democrats of west germany at first 
snubbed the weaker east german cdu and de maiziere fearing they 
were too tainted by long links with the communists 
de maiziere boldly risked alienating voters by acknowledging 
early on that the cdu had received funds from the communist party 
he earned credibility 
once accepted by west german chancellor helmut kohls party de 
maiziere fell in line with the west german cdus wishes and came 
out in favor of quick unification 
with a clear mandate to seek unification de maiziere set about 
opening coalition talks under the shadow of links with the hated 
stasi as the disbanded communist secret police was known there 
have been allegations many members of the new parliament including 
de maiziere collaborated with the stasi de maiziere denied the 
allegations 
he also has faced charges he is too close to the kohl government 
and will not protect east german interests during unification talks 
later this year 
however he dispelled some doubts when he opposed a west german 
central bank proposal to convert east german marks to west german 
marks at a 21 conversion rate de maiziere said he wants a 11 
conversion 
