motorists fuming over noxious tailpipe 
emissions on southern california roads are becoming smog snitches 
in record numbers officials said 
calls last month to the smog snitch hotline at the south coast 
air quality management district in el monte jumped 152 percent over 
march 1989 totals spokesman tom eichhorn said wednesday 
air quality officials attribute the success partly to a 100000 
billboard advertising campaign which shows a car belching dense 
black smoke beneath the words report this crime 1800 cut smog 
it has been a dynamite ad campaign for us eichhorn said 
the regional smog control agency placed 125 billboard ads 
throughout its jurisdiction in los angeles orange san bernardino 
and riverside counties 
you drive all the time in your car and youre always following 
all these obnoxious cars and trucks said one tipster kathleen 
