have become a way of life on southern california freeways 
dona dower traffic reporter for knxam radio in los angeles 
says she typically gets 75 to 100 calls a day about traffic 
conditions from commuters with cellular car phones 
regular callers often adopt pseudonyms such as mr smog man 
or mr ed and report as many as 30 tailpipe polluters a month 
said bruce collins manager of the districts smoking vehicle 
program 
last month smog hotline operators received a record 17671 
calls compared with 7000 received in the previous march 
about 150000 complaints have been received since the hotline 
was established in june 1988 collins added 
after receiving a license plate number phoned in by a tipster 
the district tracks down the vehicles registered owner and mails a 
warning that driving an excessively smoking motor vehicle is a 
violation 
