1954 and was elected to congress in 1956 at 33 moore was the 
youngest freshman in the 85th congress and represented the states 
northern panhandle for six terms 
in 1968 moore gave up his house seat to run for governor he 
was injured two days before the election when his helicopter 
crashed at a political rally in hamlin he made a brief statement 
to the crowd before being rushed to the hospital and many political 
observers credit that event for helping him win 
in august 1979 his former state liquor commissioner j richard 
barber was convicted of racketeering extortion and mail fraud 
the conviction involved charges that barber received cash and free 
liquor from distillers while serving as moores commissioner of 
alcohol beverage control 
the trial included testimony that some of the cash was used for 
campaign contributions and some of the liquor was passed on to the 
governors office barber was sentenced to three years in prison 
moore was the second west virginia governor to encounter legal 
trouble former democratic gov ww wally barron who served 
from 1961 to 1965 and several of his associates were tried on 
bribery conspiracy charges in 1968 barron was acquitted but later 
went to prison for bribing the foreman of the us district court 
jury that acquitted him 
