hes in excellent spirits said dr paul kornblith the 
neurologist who treated atwater at montefiore medical center 
hes quite enthusiastic hes gaining strength physically 
kornblith led a team that implanted radioactive isotopes in the 
tumor on the right side of atwaters brain physicians hope the 
isotopes will halt the growth of the tumor and kill the cancerous 
cells 
the 39yearold atwater also is undergoing chemotherapy 
treatments designed to destroy any tumor cells on the periphery of 
the lesion 
