east germanys parliament chose lothar de 
maiziere as prime minister on thursday and embraced his sweeping 
agenda for quickly uniting the foundering nation with west germany 
the former communist nations first freely elected legislature 
also apologized to jews for nazi atrocities and promised to make 
reparations to israel and seek diplomatic ties 
by putting de maizieres broad coalition government in power 
the parliament sets up a transitional government whose prime goal 
will be to negotiate the terms of creating a single germany 
before parliament met members of the coalition agreed that a 
united germany should remain part of nato and that east germany 
should merge its weak currency with west germanys strong 
deutschmark by july 1 
the coalition also backed a rapid process for unification 
however it demanded too that east germans retain some social 
benefits including housing and job guarantees as the nation of 16 
million residents sheds four decades of socialism for the 
competitive free market 
the historic decisions on thursday will be followed in the 
coming weeks by unification talks with west germany and the four 
world war ii allies that divided the countries the soviet union 
united states britain and france 
de maiziere closely aligned to helmut kohl appeared to 
distance himself from the west german chancellor after the 
parliamentary session 
he said final unification may not come late next year as kohl 
has said it can be realistic but it doesnt have to be 
realistic he said of kohls prediction 
de maiziere said merging the nations will depend less on timing 
than on the conditions he said on west germanys zdf television 
network that we must create compatible structures 
the 400member parliament put de maiziere and his 24member 
cabinet in power by a vote of 265108 with nine abstentions 
eighteen lawmakers were absent 
with the vote the new government replaces the communist 
caretaker government that has been running the economically 
troubled country since east germans overthrew the hardline regime 
of erich honecker in october 
in a remarkable string of conciliatory gestures the parliament 
recognized the legitimacy of polands postwar borders which 
include former german lands and apologized for east germanys role 
in the sovietled invasion of czechoslovakia in 1968 
it apologized for the deaths of 20 million soviets during world 
war ii and ended four decades of denials that east germanys 
former stalinist leaders played any role in the deaths of 6 million 
jews 
