<TEXT>
august wilson says the piano lesson winner 
of the 1990 pulitzer prize for drama was a a joyful play to 
write 
i wrote the play in several months and when it went around 
the country for two years i continued to work on it said the 
man who won his first pulitzer three years ago for fences 
wilson said the idea for the piano lesson which opens 
monday at broadways walter kerr theater came to him from a 
painting by black artist romare bearden the painters work 
inspired another wilson play joe turners come and gone 
bearden is a tremendous artist and i always wanted to make my 
plays worthy of his canvasses wilson said i would be doing a 
good thing if i could make them as rich and as full as the life he 
expressed in his paintings 
the playwright was taken by a bearden painting of a young girl 
sitting at a piano with her teacher standing over her from it he 
fashioned a family drama of a brother and a sister in pittsburgh in 
1936 the brother wants to buy the land his grandfather worked on 
as a slave and is willing to sell the family heirloom a piano to 
pay for it the sister wants to keep it 
wilson says he was haunted by the question can you acquire a 
sense of selfworth by denying your past 
nd when i began to work on the play it began to take on a 
larger question what do you do with your legacy and how do you 
put it to work for you 
the piano lesson is a better play for having had the 
opportunity to tour for so long before coming to new york the 
playwright said 
when it started i never said what happened to the piano 
the playwright said and i found that the audiences wanted to 
know now i do answer the question i found i did not want to make 
a choice but i discovered the choice was built into the play 
wilson was in a manhattan hotel giving an interview when he 
learned he had won the pulitzer 
i was very surprised he said i wasnt expecting it i 
thought wow this is no 2 it made me want to go right to my 
typewriter and start another one 
the piano lesson is part of a cycle of plays about black 
american life during the decades of this century its also the 
fourth collaboration between wilson and director lloyd richards 
who also directed fences 
their relationship started with ma raineys black bottom 
which opened on broadway in 1984 it was followed to new york by 
fences in 1987 and joe turners come and gone in 1988 
wilsons newest play two trains running recently opened at 
the yale repertory theater in new haven conn and eventually is 
expected to make its way to broadway 
when he returns to his home in st paul minn after the 
opening of the piano lesson wilson said he would begin work on 
moon going down set in the 1940s 
wilson is the first playwright since edward albee to win two 
pulitzer prizes for drama other twotime winners include robert 
sherwood george s kaufman and tennessee williams eugene oneill 
won four pulitzers including a posthumous award in 1957 for long 
days journey into night 
