chance as anybody else voss said 
it all started when coughlin was at city hall paying his water 
bill last summer he noticed a message on the back of the bill 
saying the water was being tested for a variety of chemicals he 
suggested that ms gray a former insurance agent with three years 
journalism experience look into it 
in september when the newspaper first reported that the 
drinking water contained nine times the safe level of 
trihalomethanes which are known to cause cancer town officials 
said ms grays article exaggerated the danger 
but 10 days after the stories began state officials told 
residents to stop drinking water from the pamlico river the marine 
corps set up 24houraday water wagons 
a second chemical even more deadly was found by state 
officials who warned that the risk of cancer for lifelong water 
drinkers could be 1 in 250 
a month later state officials found similar contaminants 
exceeding federal standards in 13 other small communities 
