what we had 
im ecstatic he said this is a dream come true its the 
pinnacle of the profession for a small town newspaper to compete 
and take home the biggest and the best is unbelieveable 
the twomonth water ban was lifted after the city began spending 
14000 per month on a temporary treatment system using chemicals 
besides chlorine the water now meets federal standards and state 
officials are working with the other towns to clean up their water 
state health director ron levine credits the daily news with the 
regulatory changes that perhaps saved hundreds of lives 
some town officials disagree with the honor and remain bitter 
about the stories that divided this quiet waterfront town as part 
of their stories ms gray and voss reported that town officials 
had known about the problem for eight years and hadnt told anyone 
washingtons elected officials have since been voted out 
