toxic waste a year to the plant the past four years 
there was no comment from american cyanamid which did not 
return repeated telephone calls 
in a statement released in london greenpeace said workers at 
the plant are regularly exposed to mercury fumes and have suffered 
a variety of mental disorders mercury attacks the central nervous 
system and can cause brain damage 
in a statement carried in the greenpeace press release the 
south african environmental group earthlife said black workers at 
thor chemicals have been sent home from the plant after suffering 
from bouts of madness associated with mercury poisoning 
bill garrard managing director of thor chemicals was quoted as 
telling the british newspaper the guardian that workers are tested 
weekly for contamination and are taken off the job if they show 
high mercury levels 
the greenpeace statement also said sediment taken from the 
nearby umgeni river showed mercury levels of 1000 parts per 
million villagers in the governmentdesignated homeland of kwazulu 
use the water for bathing washing and drinking 
this is an astonishing level of contamination among the 
highest ever recorded dr paul johnston an aquatic toxicologist 
at queen mary college in london was quoted as saying in the 
greenpeace statement 
johnston was quoted by the guardian as saying the mercury 
contamination was extensive and serious and that levels were 
hundreds of times above the world health organizations maximum 
acceptable levels for drinking water 
the kwazulu homeland in the southeastern part of south africa is 
home to 7 million blacks south africa is the only nation that 
recognizes the area as independent 
greenpeace said the toxic waste has been introduced into the 
water supply when heavy rains carry contaminated soil into the 
river 
chris priestley a spokesman for thor chemicals accused 
greenpeace of sensationalism he said if his company was 
contaminating water high mercury levels would also be present in 
drinking water in durban about 50 miles downstream 
priestley said the high levels of mercury in the soil samples 
was due to a form of gold mining called mercury leaching used in a 
nearby mine a few years ago 
he said excess mercury seaped into the river from the abandoned 
mine and contaminated the nearby zulu areas but not durban which 
is too far downstream for the contamination to affect 
i have no evidence that leads me to believe that any 
contamination that is arising is coming from thor chemicals itself 
we must now investigate and find out why this is happening 
priestley said 
in the last two years the growing trade in hazardous waste has 
prompted a number of agreements on dumping in africa in december 
1989 the european community signed a waste trade ban with 68 
african caribbean and pacific states 
in may 1988 and july 1989 the organization of african unity 
adopted resolutions calling for a toxic waste import ban for africa 
south africa is banned from membership in these groups due to 
the governments practice of racial discrimination 
</TEXT>
