to me and my family i know i have their understanding and love 
for that i shall be ever grateful 
moores democratic successor gov gaston caperton said he 
hoped west virginians now realize that he inherited a government 
that was morally bankrupt as well as financially the backroom 
slipshod politics of the past must forever remain in the past he 
said 
it was the second time moore was indicted for alleged 
improprieties in office he and his 1972 campaign manager were 
indicted in december 1975 on a charge of extorting 25000 from the 
president of a shaky financial holding company trying to get a 
state charter for a new bank he was acquitted in 1976 
moore is the latest west virginia politician in recent years to 
either become involved in a corruption scandal or resign since 
december 1988 a state attorney general a state treasurer two 
state senate presidents a senate majority leader a top aide to a 
senate president a house member and two lobbyists have lost their 
jobs 
under the plea arrangement moore agreed to help federal 
prosecutors in their investigation of political corruption in west 
virginia carey declined to provide specific cases for which moore 
would provide information 
the us attorney said his office would make no recommendation 
to the federal judge who sentences moore he said however the 
judge would be given details of other crimes moore allegedly 
committed that are not included in thursdays indictment 
moore is accused of blocking a federal grand jurys 
investigation of him last year and this year carey said 
the obstruction of justice charges allege he falsified documents 
and tried to persuade witnesses to commit perjury carey said he 
also lied in an interview with federal investigators the 
indictment alleged 
in early january 1990 moore met with former aide john leaberry 
who was moores 1988 campaign manager the indictment said 
unknown to moore his meeting with leaberry was recorded 
the indictment said in the meeting moore discussed the fact 
that he had received and used illegal cash in the 1988 campaign and 
then told leaberry how they would both falsely deny to 
investigators and to the grand jury that there had been any such 
cash in the campaign 
the indictment also alleged moore used his office to extort 
approximately 573000 in 1985 from h paul kizer and maben energy 
corp a coal mining and processing company carey said 
moore agreed to assist kizer and maben energy with receiving a 
refund of more than 2 million from the states black lung fund 
which provides benefits to coal miners with the respiratory 
disease the indictment said 
in return moore received about 25 percent of that refund it 
said the indictment said kizer was responsible for a maben energy 
check being mailed to an unidentified attorney who took 50000 as 
his share and sent the remainder to moore carey declined to 
identify the lawyer involved 
kizer is cooperating with federal prosecutors said his 
attorney james lees 
the indictment said moore created fake backdated documents 
purporting to be legitimate contingent fee legal agreements to 
cover up the extortion 
the indictment also accused moore of filing false income tax 
returns in 1984 and 1985 carey said it said he failed to report 
40000 in income in 1984 and 105000 in 1985 
moore also was charged with scheming to defraud the state of his 
salary and benefits by funneling approximately 100000 in cash 
into his 1984 campaign fund carey said 
carey said he did not know when moore would be arraigned but 
said it probably would be within 10 to 14 days 
moore whose 67th birthday is monday was the first west 
virginia governor elected to two fouryear terms and the first 
elected to three serving from 1969 to 1977 and from 1985 to 1989 
moore survived three decades of west virginias roughandtumble 
politics despite a 2to1 registration edge for the democrats and 
almost constant controversy 
he served one term in the state house of delegates from 1953 to 
1954 and was elected to congress in 1956 at 33 moore was the 
youngest freshman in the 85th congress and represented the states 
northern panhandle for six terms 
in 1968 moore gave up his house seat to run for governor he 
was prevented from seeking a third consecutive term by a provision 
of the state constitution and was succeeded by democrat jay 
rockefeller in january 1977 
moore was dogged by controversy even out of office 
in august 1979 his former state liquor commissioner j richard 
barber was convicted of racketeering extortion and mail fraud 
involving charges that barber received cash and free liquor from 
distillers the trial included testimony that some of the cash was 
used for campaign contributions and some of the liquor was passed 
on to the governors office barber was sentenced to three years in 
prison 
moore won the governorship for the third time in 1984 however 
in that term moore presided over a state government in extreme 
financial difficulty unable to pay its bills and forced to borrow 
heavily 
his tenure ended in dramatic defeat when democratic newcomer 
gaston caperton routed him in the 1988 election 
</TEXT>
