<TEXT>
exiled king michael of romania was barred from 
returning to his homeland thursday when the romanian government 
canceled his visa and said the monarchs first visit in 43 years 
might promote unrest 
the 68yearold exking told an airport news conference in 
zurich switzerland his visit would have been strictly private 
i dont understand the decision to rescind the visas i dont 
know what concerns there could have been he declared he was to 
have been accompanied by his wife queen anne and his eldest 
daughter princess margarita their visas were also rescinded 
romanias provisional postrevolutionary government had 
appealed to michael to postpone his visit until after may 20 
elections to prevent possible disturbances 
in bucharest several hundred romanians who had gathered to 
welcome the exking broke into chants of shame shame and 
down with the communists when they heard he was not coming 
the king was booked on a swissair flight from zurich to 
bucharest thursday at noon but the airline management decided not 
to let him board the plane he learned of the cancellation of the 
visas only after leaving his home near geneva 
in an interview with frances staterun antenne 2 television 
channel thursday romanian prime minister petre roman said michael 
had planned to attend a demonstration in the western city of 
timisoara where the december revolution began he said the visit 
would have been covered by about 80 journalists flown in especially 
by chartered plane 
thus it was not at all a private visit which we would not 
have objected to but a visit of a political character which was 
opposed by practically all political factions and by public 
opinion roman said 
silviu brucan chief ideologue of the national salvation front 
the dominant power in romanias provisional government called the 
visit a very controversial political issue 
we are striving to calm down public opinion brucan said 
referring to the ethnic violence in transylvania last month that 
left at least six people dead 
on wednesday the bucharest government warned in a statement 
that there is the possibility of some violent manifestations if 
the visit took place 
it said michaels visit before the elections could exacerbate 
existing conflicts while also endangering his personal security 
when asked at the airport to speculate on bucharests motives 
michael said he had no idea at this moment but he said he was 
still planning a visit as soon as possible 
in romania princess helen one of michaels five daughters 
said no words can express the sorrow of my father at being 
barred from romania during easter celebrations she and her sister 
sophie arrived in the country a few days ago with aid shipments 
michaels other daughters margarita anne and marie live in 
exile 
michael was forced to abdicate by a sovietinstalled government 
dec 30 1947 he had intended to stay no longer than 10 days in 
romania 
michael who has been living near geneva for the past 30 years 
denounced his abdication shortly after he arrived in exile saying 
he signed the act after being told a refusal would set off a 
massacre of his supporters 
after the overthrow of communist dictator nicolae ceausescu in 
december michael said he was prepared to return to romania as head 
of a constitutional monarchy but he indicated that this would have 
to be subject to a referendum 
