<TEXT>
daniel patrick moynihans career hasnt fit 
the traditional pattern while most senators work to change votes 
he works to change minds 
so theres no moynihan act or moynihan amendment to mark the 
pinnacle of his senate tenure his is a different approach 
wholesale instead of retail 
what moynihan loves to do is take an idea pluck it out of the 
heavens set it on the table and let it influence events says 
rep charles schumer dny 
the former professor diplomat and white house official has done 
it time and again he puts forward an idea that at first goes 
against common wisdom but stays alive despite efforts by others to 
proclaim it dead 
in the 1960s as an official first in democratic and then 
republican administrations moynihan wrote about the instability of 
black family life and its harmful effects on blacks chance of 
success controversial at first his ideas two decades later drove 
the 1988 welfare reform act 
after president ford made him united nations ambassador in 1975 
moynihan rocked the diplomatic corps by bluntly asserting us 
positions he was particularly sharptongued in opposing a 
resolution labeling zionism as a form of racism he stayed only 
eight months before returning to harvard but he established the 
model for his us successors at the world body 
in 1976 he was elected to the senate giving up his 
professorship but he has clung to the image of an academician 
tall grayhaired and tweedclothed he seems able to lecture his 
colleagues on an infinite range of topics 
hes never had an unspoken thought quipped one colleague 
his occasional meetings with washington reporters are called 
tutorials by the attendees who sit in chairs arranged 
classroomlike in his office 
he doesnt just answer questions he expounds on most anything 
at one recent session he described the life cycle of the sea 
lamprey a parasitic fish whose control he supports noting that it 
was really a nice piece of biology 
unlike many lawmakers the burden of elected office has not 
dampened moynihans taste for the controversial his latest idea on 
social security has revitalized that penchant 
back in 1983 moynihan was the intellectual force behind an 
increase in social security payroll taxes so that the system could 
build up a surplus for when the baby boom generation retires 
the surplus is now building at a rate of 1 billion a week but 
instead of being saved for the future as moynihan intended its 
being frittered away to cover daytoday government operating 
expenses and make the federal deficit appear smaller 
washingtons leaders promise to make the surplus offbudget 
and thus more sacrosanct but in reality that answer is nothing 
more than how you display your books moynihan says 
his solution roll back the payroll tax simple but the 
political implications are immense 
the white house and even some fellow democrats such as house 
ways and means chairman dan rostenkowski dill label the idea as 
dangerous the politicians dont like to admit that social security 
taxes are being misused but nobody seems willing to cut spending 
or raise other taxes enough to take their place 
some fretted with prodding from president bush that the plan 
was somehow messing with social security a political nono 
one official even called it goofy but the biggest white house 
worry was that a democrat was treading on turf the republicans 
thought they owned tax cuts 
unlike bushs cherished capital gains tax cut moynihans 
benefits would be tilted to the working poor and middle class 
political genius is what democratic national committee 
chairman ronald brown called it last month just when congress 
