<TEXT>
bond prices slipped thursday in light 
preholiday trading with little economic news to affect the 
direction of the market traders said 
the treasurys benchmark 30year bond fell 732 point or about 
219 for every 1000 in face amount its yield which rises when 
the price declines rose to 859 percent from 857 percent late 
wednesday 
traders said a retail sales report released by the government 
thursday morning initially boosted treasury prices because the 
march sales figure was weaker than expected an indication of 
economic sluggishness boosts bonds because it implies the federal 
reserve may act to ease interest rates 
but news that the government revised the february retail sales 
figure upward from an 08 percent decline to an 03 percent 
decline caused bond prices to give up their gains 
tom lanier a treasury bond trader for manufacturers hanover 
trust co said there was little activity in the market 
theres no buying going on and we keep getting hit by 
supply he said referring to the treasurys scheduled 
announcements next week on upcoming bill and note auctions and an 
announcement thursday from resolution trust corp the governments 
thrift bailout agency on its bond auction plans 
the rtc said it may sell up to 427 billion in bonds this 
quarter about 20 billion more than wall street thought it would 
try to sell lanier said 
news of an increased supply of bonds can send prices lower for 
fear of a temporary oversupply but lanier said the effect on 
prices thursday was minimal 
traders said there was little economic news to affect the market 
all week the important wholesale price index for march will be 
released friday when the market will be closed for the good friday 
holiday 
traders said the market virtually shut down about 2 pm edt in 
advance of the day off 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
government issues fell from 116 point to 332 point intermediate 
maturities dropped from 532 to 732 point and longterm issues 
fell 732 point according to telerate inc a financial 
information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer fell 113 to 115001 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds was unchanged at 91 716 the average yield 
to maturity rose to 772 percent from 751 percent last wednesday 
yields on threemonth treasury bills remained at 8 percent as 
the discount held at 775 percent yields on sixmonth bills rose 
to 819 percent as the discount rose 2 basis points to 777 
percent yields on oneyear bills rose to 826 percent as the 
discount rose 1 basis point to 768 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest rate banks charge each 
other on overnight loans was quoted at 8lsqb percent unchanged from 
late wednesday 
</TEXT>
